Question: How to read from a file in reverse order?: I have a file of unknown size and I want to read it in reverse order. I know that I can read the whole file into memory and then reverse it, but I want to avoid this if possible. Is there a way to do this using Java NIO's FileChannel?
Please using this api: FileChannel.position.
Answer:<<<api>>>: FileChannel.position
<<<code>>>: long fileSize = fileChannel.size();
while(fileSize >= 0) {
    try{
        fileChannel.position(fileSize);
        byte b = fileChannel.readByte();
        System.out.println(b);
        fileSize--;
    } catch {System.out.println("Something went wrong.");}
}
<<<explanation>>>: You can use FileChannel.position() to move the position of the file pointer to a specific position in the file. You can then use FileChannel.readByte() to read a byte from the file. By moving the file pointer one byte at a time from the end of the file to the beginning, you can read the file in reverse order.
